OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F433A1776780669
OL,3,CAt least two children die each month
OL,4,Cfrom knife injuries in England, study
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FAt least two school-aged children die
OL,8,Feach month from knife injuries in
OL,9,FEngland, according to the first
OL,10,Fnational analysis of its kind carried
OL,11,Fout by the University of Bristol.
OL,13,FThe research reveals that most
OL,14,Ffatalities happen from a single stab
OL,15,Fwound, and young people of black or
OL,16,Fblack British ethnicity are more
OL,17,Flikely to die of knife-related injury
OL,18,Fthan children and young people who are
OL,19,Fwhite.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
